  "texts": [
    "Agents run independently and do not directly communicate with each other.",
    "They take work entities such as tasks and jobs from the database, perform actions on them, and update the database.",
    "Each agent is designed around a plugin structure with the experiment-agnostic core and plugins.",
    "Plugins are software add-ons to enhance JEDI's capabilities to perform experiment-specific functions, such as interfacing with experiment-specific external services and performing actions required for the experiment-specific usecases.",
    "It is possible to configure JEDI instances to load new plugins and add new features.The exclusive lock mechanism allows operations to be distributed across threads, processes, and instances, so that JEDI horizontally scales with multiple instances."
  ],
